# Berezovka, Bizhbulyaksky District, Republic of Bashkortostan

}}
Berezovka () is a rural locality (a village) in Aitovsky Selsoviet, Bizhbulyaksky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 7 as of 2010. There are 2 streets.
Geography
Berezovka is located 36&nbsp;km southwest of Bizhbulyak (the district's administrative centre) by road. Alexeyevka is the nearest rural locality.
